  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for the administrative secretary in the office of the general secretary</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The south Sudan council of churches is in the process of implementation of the action plan for peace through delivery of 4 programme outcomes relating to advocacy, neutral forum, reconciliation and institutional capacity strengthening. through this church based , nation-wide and multi-stakeholder engagement action, the south sudan council of churches envisages the realisation of a peaceful resolution of conflict and restoration of peace in south sudan. the first phase of the action plan for peace 2016-2017 has ended and SSCC is now implementing a new phase 2018-2021 through annual funding of ecumenical partners including Norwegian church aid, catholic relief service, Finn church aid, CAFOD andTrocaire partnership and Christian aid and PAX , all working collaboratively under the structure core group whose work is to mobile funding and provide technical support to SSCC in the implementation of the APP.</narrative>
  </description>
